#week-title("Four", "Bare Receptivity & Integration")

=== Core Teaching

The Philosophic Mercury in the inner work corresponds to *Receptivity* — the
quality of mind that neither grasps nor rejects, but receives. This is the mental
parallel to the universal solvent.

Just as the Philosophic Mercury dissolves whatever it touches without being
destroyed by it, the receptive mind can observe thoughts and feelings without
becoming attached to them. This week is about mastering this "bare receptivity"
before we move into the complex astrology of Quarter II.

=== Topics This Week

- The psychology of the Philosophic Mercury
- Receptivity vs. Passivity
- Integration of the first Quarter's water work

#inner-work[
  *Bare Receptivity Practice*

  Practice a daily 20-minute meditation on bare receptivity.
  - *The Practice:* Sit. Have no object, no goal, no visualisation. Simply be
    open to whatever arises — sound, thought, sensation — without acting upon it.
  
  If the mind "grasps" a thought, notice it and release the grip. Record how this
  state of mind impacts your perception of the water in your flasks.
]

